videos.headline: Iowa starts second straight game with pick-six
videos.description: Iowa's Joshua Jackson intercepts Alex Hornibrook's pass and returns it 43 yards as the Hawkeyes fly to a 7-0 lead.

videos.headline: Hornibrook and Davis connect for Wisconsin first down
videos.description: Wisconsin's Alex Hornibrook fires in a throw to  Danny Davis III for 16 yards to set up a Badgers' field goal.

videos.headline: Gervase hauls in Iowa interception
videos.description: Iowa's Jake Gervase is not fooled by Wisconsin's play-action and comes down with the interception on the Iowa 6-yard line.

videos.headline: Pryor takes end-around to the house for Wisconsin TD
videos.description: Wisconsin's Kendric Pryor gets the ball deep in the backfield and follows his blockers 25 yards for the score to give the Badgers a 10-7 lead.

videos.headline: Iowa punches ball loose and recovers
videos.description: Joshua Jackson forces another turnover by punching the ball while tackling Jonathan Taylor.

videos.headline: Wisconsin's Pryor climbs the ladder for second score
videos.description: Wisconsin's Alex Hornibrook throws it up for Kendric Pryor who elevates over his Iowa defender to come down with the touchdown as the Badgers lead 17-7 before half.

videos.headline: Chryst 'proud' of team's reponse
videos.description: After throwing a pick-six on their first drive, Wisconsin head coach Paul Chryst likes the way his team responded offensively and defensively, but would like to see less turnovers.

videos.headline: Joshua Jackson is a scoring machine for Iowa defense
videos.description: Iowa's Joshua Jackson intercepts Alex Hornibrook and returns it for his second pick-six today and cuts the deficit to 17-14 for Iowa.

videos.headline: Early snap results in Wisconsin TD
videos.description: Iowa quarterback Nathan Stanley is pointing at defenders when the ball is snapped, and the ball squirts behind the pile where Wisconsin's Leon Jacobs scoops it and scores.

videos.headline: Edwards dives and deflects ball to himself for INT
videos.description: Wisconsin's T.J. Edwards sits in the zone and dives to intercept  Nathan Stanley in Wisconsin territory.

videos.headline: Davis concentrates to make 28-yard catch in bounds
videos.description: Wisconsin's Danny Davis III turns his body around to make the sideline catch and keeps a foot in bounds to put the Badgers in the red zone.

videos.headline: Shaw beats Hawkeyes defense to the pylon
videos.description: Wisconsin's Bradrick Shaw gets the handoff and sprints to the pylon to score from 8 yards out as the Badgers lead 31-14.

videos.headline: Jacobs recovers second fumble for Wisconsin
videos.description: The Wisconsin pass rush forces Nathan Stanley to step up in the pocket and he loses grip of the ball giving Wisconsin possession with good field position.

videos.headline: Hornibrook connects with Taylor for 4th quarter Badger TD
videos.description: Wisconsin's quarterback Alex Hornibrook hangs in the pocket and delivers a strike to A.J. Taylor as the Badgers take a 38-14 lead.

videos.headline: Chryst: 'Defense played lights out'
videos.description: Wisconsin's defense held Iowa to be 0-13 on third down conversions as the Badgers clinch the West division in the Big Ten.

videos.headline: Crazy fumble sparks Wisconsin's run to victory over Iowa
videos.description: Go inside Wisconsin's fumble recovery that led to a blowout victory over the Hawkeyes.
